            "body": "> Did you try that?\r\n\r\nI didn't try it (because I don't think there's a good way to test it in advance) but I believe it does.\r\n\r\nI was trying to avoid putting a hard version pin in pyproject.toml because that forces the strict version check onto user when they probably don't care.\r\n\r\nI agree about the no-isolation though.  That sounds like `PIP_BUILD_CONSTRAINT` might be the better solution here.",
